name: Chicken Tetrazzini
author: Nicole Leonard
summary: This yummy dish can also be made with chopped ham or turkey (a great use for Thanksgiving leftovers)!
ingredients: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  cream of chicken soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil
Cook spaghetti in the boiling water until cooked through but firm to the bite, about 12 minutes; drain
Melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat

Cook and stir onion in melted margarine until soft and translucent, 5 to 7 minutes; add to the spaghetti along with chicken, evaporated milk, cream of chicken soup, 4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese, celery salt, salt, and black pepper
Toss mixture to evenly mix; transfer to prepared dish
Sprinkle 4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese over spaghetti mixture
Bake in preheated oven until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbling, about 45 minutes
